Ball Corp said it was awarded aone-year 12,750,000 dlr contract to supply copper-plated zincpenny blanks to the U.S. mints in Philadelphia and Denver.    The new contract, effective in June, calls for shipping23,200,000 pounds of blanks to the mint in Philadelphia and7,600,000 pounds to Denver. It said the blanks will bemanufactured in Greenville, Tenn.    Ball began supplying blanks to the San Francisco and WestPoint mints in 1981 when the penny's content was changed tozinc from copper. Reuter&#3;